      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS BLUE STORK (2) was very brave last start when she drew widest and was forced to work when covering ground but fought on for a 1.9m second at Menangle. Had won twice in row from wider barriers than this prior, one of them at this circuit and distance. Should get every chance from this draw. CROWN MOJO (4) is in good form. Came from the outside barrier when third at his latest appearance at Menangle and had missed by just a neck when runner-up at this circuit and distance prior. Big chance. FLO RYDA NZ (9) draws on the second line but is in contention backing up after cruising home by 15 metres at Bankstown on Monday. GREY CADILLAC (8) draws on the back row but is tough to leave out on the back of three successive wins.",
